        "Status": "Active",
        "Project/Activity Summary - Story Content": "For more than 25 years, Colorado State University and Lincoln University have sustained a dynamic exchange partnership that offers students an immersive, hands-on international learning experience. Participants study in a close-knit academic environment known for its strengths in agriculture, environmental systems, and sustainability, while engaging in field-based coursework and exploring the diverse landscapes of New Zealand.\nEach spring semester, a CSU Faculty-in-Residence accompanies students, providing on-site academic support and fostering a strong sense of community abroad. The program also allows students to earn transferable credits while gaining a global perspective and building international networks.\nIn 2025, the partnership expanded to include a U.S.-based ranch internship funded by Angus New Zealand, offering participants hands-on industry experience and a unique opportunity to connect international study with applied agricultural practice.\n",
