        "Project/Activity Summary - Story Content": "Professor Jessica Prenni’s international research collaborations are centered on the Periodic Table of Food Initiative (PTFI), which aims to standardize the characterization of food composition across the world’s edible biodiversity. Her work involves analytical studies of foods and close collaboration with international partners, including training in laboratory methods, joint data analysis, and co-authorship of scientific publications. Through these efforts, she contributes to building a global research ecosystem focused on improving understanding of food quality to address interconnected challenges in human and planetary health. Her collaborations also emphasize education, mentorship, and capacity building for early-career scientists, particularly in the Global South.\n",
