        "Date Added": "2026-03-25",
        "Project/Activity Summary - Story Content": "This CSU faculty-led fall semester program takes students to live and learn in Florence, Italy. Students are able to study Food & Resource Economics through experiential learning opportunities that go beyond the traditional classroom setting.  \nFlorence is located in the Tuscany region of Italy, on the banks of the Arno River, surrounded by the rolling hills of the Italian countryside. The city has the essence of the Renaissance and stands out for its culture and history. Florence museums, palaces and churches house some of the greatest artistic treasures in the world.  \nCoursework integrates economics, policy, and culture, exploring how Italian food and resource-based industries are shaped by history, markets, and sustainability practices. Students engage in experiential learning through field-based activities and required excursions that connect classroom concepts to real-world contexts across Florence and the surrounding countryside. \nBeyond academics, participants experience daily life in Italy—gaining firsthand insight into local food systems, regional culture, and the role of place in economic development—while building a global perspective on agriculture, sustainability, and international markets.\n",
