        "Project/Activity Summary - Story Content": "The University of Glasgow's School of Veterinary Medicine, has an internationally renowned reputation in Veterinary Medicine, and is fully accredited by the AVMA. CSU is working with The University of Glasgow to offer a unique opportunity for high quality animal science and equine science students who wish to study veterinary medicine within the global context.\nSelected students will study the final year of their animal science/equine science degree at the University of Glasgow as a study abroad opportunity. During their time at Glasgow, CSU students will study alongside students in their first year of the University of Glasgow’s veterinary medicine degree programme (Bachelor of Veterinary Medicine and Surgery, BVMS – which is the equivalent to the DVM).\n",
